<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 9 Killed in Traffic Accident in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Nine people were killed and
five others injured in a collision between a van and a lorry in
India's Karnataka state on Monday night, Press Trust of India
reported today.
</P>
<P>
While seven persons died on the spot, two succumbed to injuries
at a local hospital, police said.
</P>
<P>
This is the second major traffic accident in the southern
Indian state in a few days.
</P>
<P>
In a road mishap on Sunday, 20 people were killed when a lorry
overturned on a national highway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
