<DOCNO> XIE19970806.0002 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Toxic Chemicals Spill Alert After Truck Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 5 (Xinhua) -- A truck driver was seriously
injured early today after his tanker overturned on an expressway
in Japan, spilling some 1,600 liters of toxic chlorine chemicals
onto the road, the press reported.
</P>
<P>
The accident happened this morning on the Tokyo-Nagoya in
Shizuoka Prefecture when the truck hit the central barrier and
turned on its side, blocking traffic in both directions.
</P>
<P>
Rain turned the leaked fatty acid chloride into chlorine gas
and emergency warnings were broadcast to local residents, telling
them to close their windows and stay indoors, police said.
</P>
<P>
Police highway patrol squads and local firemen spread sand and
counteragents to clean up the substance, and two other tanker
trucks were sent to the site to siphon the remaining chemical from
the overturned truck, highway patrol officials said.
</P>
<P>
The highway interchange between Yoshida and Kikugawa was closed
around 6:30 a.m.. The part of the highway carrying Tokyo-bound
traffic was reopened in the afternoon, while that to Nagoya is
expected to return to operation later in the day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
