<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Commissioner's Office, HKSAR Government Cooperate Well </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Ma Yuzhen, commissioner of the
Chinese Foreign Ministry in the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (SAR), said that his office and the SAR Government have
established a close cooperative relationship in the past month.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a meeting held tonight by the Hong Kong Chinese
General Chamber of Commerce, Ma said that, with support and
assistance from the SAR Government and Hong Kong residents from
all walks of life, his office has been operating in a quite normal
way since its establishment a month ago.
</P>
<P>
"I myself has established a close working relationship with
Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa. All the department directors in my
office have also set up communication channels with related
offices of the SAR Government," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that in the past month he has passed three letters of
authority signed by Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen
onto Tung Chee Hwa, which were about the signing of the Hong
Kong-British civil aviation agreement, negotiations on mutual
visa-free access agreement with related countries, and
negotiations with related countries on legal assistance,
investment protection and civil aviation transit agreements.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he said, the Commissioner's Office, the HKSAR
Government and the Chinese embassy in Cambodia have also been
working closely to provide consular protection and assistance to
Hong Kong residents stranded in that country during the conflict
last month.
</P>
<P>
At present the Office is working closely with the SAR
Government on preparations for the World Bank/International
Monetary Fund annual meetings to be held in Hong Kong in
September, as well as on the issue of the Vietnamese boat people.
</P>
<P>
He said the Central People's Government has granted the SAR
Government quite comprehensive authority in dealing with external
affairs and this fully demonstrates the Central Government's trust
in and support for the SAR government.
</P>
<P>
He said the Office is established to protect the country's
sovereignty and interests, including the interests of the HKSAR
and the legal rights and interests of Hong Kong residents, and
assist the SAR in developing economic, trade and other relations
with foreign countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The Commissioner's Office will strictly abide by the related
provisions in the Basic Law, and the staff in the Office will also
abide by related laws of the SAR, he added.
</P>
<P>
Ma also talked about the responsibilities of the Commissioner's
Office, the relationship between the Office and the SAR
Government, the scope of authority granted to the SAR by the
Central Government and other related matters.  
</P>
</TEXT>
