<HEADLINE> Accord to Provide World-class Information Signed in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The China Internet Corporation
and China's Ministry of Post and Telecommunications have signed a
partnership agreement designed to provide world-class business
information to Internet users across China, according to a press
release circulated here tonight.
</P>
<P>
The accord will bring the China Internet's world-leading
business information to over 100 major cities in China via
CHINANET, the ministry's nationwide Internet network and the
backbone of China's Internet infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the China Internet's China Wide Web, an
Internet information provider, will deliver comprehensive business
information from a number of world's big news agencies and
corporations to Chinese subscribers via CHINANET.
</P>
<P>
Additional joint services for the two sides will include
Corporate Solution packages, with utilization of the software and
hardware technology of the China Internet's technology partner,
the press release said, adding that the China Internet will be the
only national Internet subscription re-seller for the ministry in
all major cities across China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
