<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Samaranch Says Sport is Divided in Drug Battle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 5 (Xinhua) -- International Olympic Committee
president Juan Antonio Samaranch said on Tuesday that some
sporting organisations did nothing to catch drug cheats.
</P>
<P>
Samaranch said there was a split in international sport between
officials who wanted to catch doping offenders and those who did
not.
</P>
<P>
"I am surprised with sports that there are two different
worlds," Samaranch said. "One world with the IOC and international
federations fighting against doping.
</P>
<P>
"There is a second world where they do nothing against doping."
</P>
<P>
But he did not give the names of the countries or federations
to which he was referring. 
</P>
</TEXT>
