<HEADLINE> Iran Calls for Efforts to Bring Peace to Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Ambassador to Pakistan
Mehdi Akhoundzadeh stressed here today that Pakistan and Iran
should make concerted diplomatic efforts for the restoration of
peace in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
"We should launch joint efforts to persuade all warring
factions to come to the negotiating table for a peaceful
settlement of the Afghanistan problem," the ambassador told a
press conference held here earlier today.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his hope that Iftikhar Murshid, Pakistani foreign
secretary who left here Monday night for Tehran in a bid to
coordinate his country's Afghan policy with Iran, would be able to
promote peace initiatives in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Akhoundzadeh called upon the United Nations to
intensify its efforts to bring peace to Afghanistan and expedite
its activities for a peaceful solution of the Afghanistan problem.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador also hoped that Pakistan and Iran would further
strengthen cooperation in economic, trade and cultural fields.
</P>
</TEXT>
