<HEADLINE> Pakistani FM to Visit Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Foreign Minister
Gohar Ayub Khan will leave here for Turkey on Wednesday on a
three-day official visit to enhance bilateral relations between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Turkey Ayub Khan will hold talks with his
Turkish counterpart Ismail Cem on a wide range of regional and
international issues of common interest, official sources said.
</P>
<P>
Ayub Khan will brief Turkish leaders about the resumption of
Pakistan-India dialogue for the settlement of all outstanding
issues including the core issue of Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he will brief them about Pakistan's diplomatic
efforts to bring warring Afghan factions to the negotiation table
for peace in the country, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
He will also seek Turkey's support for holding an intra-Afghan
dialogue under the auspices of the United Nations and an
international conference on Afghanistan proposed by Pakistan for
ensuring durable peace in the war-torn country, according to the
sources.  
</P>
</TEXT>
