<HEADLINE> Palestinian Speaker Calls for End of Total </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The legislative Palestinian
Council President, Ahmed Queria, today warned of the dangerous
consequences of the week-long collective punishment by the
Israeli government of the Palestinian people.
</P>
<P>
In a written statement issued in Ramallah, Queria appealed to
the Israeli government to halt all of its arbitrary and
aggressive measures, according to a report of JMCC, a Palestinian
press service based in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Israeli government should immediately stop
"coverting 3 million Palestinians into hostages and detainees
in their cities, villages and refugee camps."
</P>
<P>
"We Palestinian people will not accept bow to be a victim of
war and expansion ideology which dominate the minds of some
Israeli leaders," Queria said.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli authorities imposed a total closure on the
Palestinian territories in the wake of a double suicide bombing
in Jerusalem Wednesday, in which 15 people were killed and 170
others wounded.
</P>
<P>
Palestinians say that the blockade has caused 5 million
U.S. dollar loss for the Palestinian economy every day.
</P>
<P>
Israel also suspended tax revenue transfer to the Palestinian
National Authority (PNA) and jam the Voice of Palestine radio
broadcast.
</P>
<P>
Regarding the U.S. role, Queria said in the statement: "If
Washington does not play its role as a neutral co-sponsor for
the peace process, it will drive the peace process to a total
collapse."
</P>
<P>
The head of the Palestinian legislature criticized the
U.S. Congress for its decision to halt financial support to the
PNA.
</P>
<P>
"Once again, the Congress is proving its hostile position
toward the Palestinian people and its prejudice in favor of the
Israeli acts of aggression," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
