<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pedroso Wins Men's Long Jump World Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 5 (Xinhua) -- World defending champion Ivan Pedroso
of Cuba retained his world title in the men's long jump final with a
8.42-meter leap at the 6th World Athletics Championships here tonight.
</P>
<P>
The silver and bronze medals were snatched by Erick Walder of the
United States at 8.38 and Kirill Sosunov of Russia at 8.18
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Pedroso, whose personal best is 8.71 meters, opened brilliantly
with his longest leap tonight, but fouled the following four jumps in a
row. His fifth round leap was about 8.70 meters, but he slightly
fouled at the jumping line.
</P>
<P>
The world indoor champion this year went all out on the final
outing, only managing a poor 7.60.
</P>
<P>
Walder chased the Cuban all the way, with a 8.29m opener, followed
by an impressive combination of 8.15, 8.29, 8.36 and 8.30.
</P>
<P>
James Beckford of Jamaica, silver medallist at both the Olympic and
the previous meet, finished fourth at 8.14. 
</P>
</TEXT>
