<DOCNO> XIE19970806.0043 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanznaian FM on UN Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania today urged the
United Nations to ensure it extends the Security Council's
permanent membership to include African, Asian and Latin American
Regions.
</P>
<P>
The Tanzanian stand was expressed by Minister for foreign
Affairs and International Cooperation Jakaya Kiwete in a speech
read by the ministry's principal secretary, Elly Mtango, at a
two-day workshop on "U.N. Reform" in the Tanzanian capital.
</P>
<P>
Kiwete said in the speech that expansion is necessary to
ensure fair representation in the Security Council.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania supports the U.N. reform but the issue of inequitable
representation in the Security Council is one of major concerns,
according to Kiwete.
</P>
<P>
Other issues of concerns listed by Kiwete are the right to
development, financial crisis of the U.N. system, restructuring
of the U.N. secretariat, coordination of the U.N. and its
specialized agencies, peace and security, economic and social
issues and humanitarian affairs.
</P>
<P>
"Most of these concerns have covered in the U..N reform
proposals which contain wide ranging recommendations on how best
the U.N. system should function in the changing world and
especially in the next millennium," the Tanzanian foreign
minister noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
