<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Urgent: S. Korean Boeing 747 Crashes off Guam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 5 (Xinhua) -- A South Korean Air jumbo jet
with 331 people aboard crashed today while trying to land on Guam.
Guam Police was reportedly saying 29 people survived.
</P>
<P>
Flight 801 was from Seoul, South Korea. It was cleared to land
at Guam when contact was lost about five kilometers from Agana
International Airport, Tom Rea, the Federal Aviation
Administration's Pacific representative in Honolulu said,
according to a local media report.
</P>
<P>
Frank Matane of Guam Police said that 29 people apparently
survived the crash of a Boeing 747 in the hills.
</P>
<P>
The FAA in Washington said Flight 801 disappeared from radar at
2:35 a.m. Wednesday, Guam time (12:35 p.m. EDT). 
</P>
</TEXT>
