<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zelezny out of Top Eight in Men's Javelin Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 5 (Xinhua) -- World record holder and defending
champion Jan Zelezny of Czech Republic had a terrible night here on
Tuesday when the hot favourite failed to enter the top eight in the
men's javelin final at the 6th World Athletics Championships.
</P>
<P>
The Czech fouled his first two throws, and messed up his technic
completedly in the third round with a 82.04-meter fling, more than 16
meters short of his 98.48m world record.
</P>
<P>
He finished 9th in the first three rounds, only the top eight
advanced to the last three throws.
</P>
<P>
"No ecuses! The day of the qualification was a good one, the day of
the final was an off one! The only problem has been my very poor
throwing technic today," said the loser after the competition.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
