<DOCNO> XIE19970806.0056 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Population Census Carried Out in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 5 (Xinhua) -- A population census is
underway in Mozambique, reports reaching here from Maputo said.
</P>
<P>
The counting is already in its fourth day, with officials
expressing satisfaction with progress made so far.
</P>
<P>
Director of Mozambican Central Census Office Joao Loureiro
said the body count is proving much easier than had been
expected.
</P>
<P>
He said his office has started sending additional materials to
the northern, central and southern regions to avoid any
disruption to the census.
</P>
<P>
Mozambique last carried out a census in 1980, when its
population was put at 16.6 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
