<HEADLINE> Mozambique Prepares for Impending Drought </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The Mozambican government
is taking precautions following predictions of drought in the
next season.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Agriculture has started to distribute
drought-resistant seeds to farmers, reports reaching here from
Maputo said.
</P>
<P>
The southern provinces of Mozambique are expected to be
seriously affected by a possible drought. But a warning has also
been sent to the northern provinces.
</P>
<P>
According to the Mozambican government, further studies are
being conducted and a firm conclusion is likely to be issued by
September, the start of the rainy season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
