<HEADLINE> Nigerian Capital Starts One-Week Free Medical </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Residents in Abuja, the Nigerian
capital are to enjoy free medical services for one week, starting
from today, the News Agency of Nigeria said.
</P>
<P>
The program was sponsored by the Family Support Program (FSP)
in conjunction with the Pro-health International. The FSP is
headed by the country First Lady Maryam Abacha and aimed at
improving the welfare of Nigerian families.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the launching ceremony today, Lieutenant-General
Jeremiah Useni, the Military Administrator of the Federal Capital
Territory urged the capital residents to take the full advantage
of the chance to improve their health. 
