<HEADLINE> World Bank Backs Bolivia Government's Decentralization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today okayed a
credit of some 15 million U.S. dollar equivalent to the Bolivian
Government to help finance the Financial Decentralization and
Accountability Project.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be channeled through the International
Development Association (IDA), the Bank's concessionary lending
arm for developing countries.
</P>
<P>
The project is aimed to modernize the Government's financial
management infrastructure and public sector auditing capability
during its transition toward a decentralization.
</P>
<P>
The project is also designed to improve efficiency of public
institutions and ensure more effective use of the country's
financial resources.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project is about 17.31 million dollars.
In addition to the IDA credit, the balance will be provided by the
government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
