<DOCNO> XIE19970806.0072 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uganda, Tanzania to Boost Coop in Transport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri
Moseveni said today that his country will boost cooperations in
road and water transport with neighboring Tanzania in a bid to
link the east African region with the rest of Africa.
</P>
<P>
In a speech opening bilateral talks here, Moseveni said,
Uganda and Tanzania are linked both culturally and politically,
especially in the struggle against foreign domination.
</P>
<P>
Uganda is ready to discuss all matters with Tanzania
particularly on the issue of road and water transport, the
Ugandan president added.
</P>
<P>
He revealed that Uganda and Kenya are trying to solve some
transport issues in the region of Mount Elgon to link the region
with Ethiopia, whereas Uganda and the Democratic Republic of
Congo (formerly Zaire) will soon meet to map out how to improve
road transport between areas of western Uganda and eastern Congo.
</P>
<P>
If the projected road program in the region is realized, the
continent of Africa will be linked, Museveni said.
</P>
<P>
Visiting Tanzanian President Benjamin Mkapa, on his part,
pointed out that projects of cooperation between the two
countries are for their mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
Stressing the importance of exchanges between the private
sectors of the two countries, Mkapa noted that the current
Tanzanian delegation for bilateral talks has included businessmen
and enterpreneurs.
</P>
<P>
Mkapa said he is confident that his visit will further promote
the cause of peace and stability in the whole region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
