expected to leave for their various destinations tonight by a
special flight, local radio reported here this evening.
</P>
<P>
All 117 passengers who survived the crash are reportedly doing
fine, including nine who are still in hospital though not in
crucial condition.
</P>
<P>
Investigations into the cause of the crash will soon kick off.
</P>
<P>
The Air Africa plane accident occurred on Sunday night at the
Douala International Airport.
</P>
<P>
The plane, just came in from Abidjan, had 117 passengers and a
crew of seven on board who were on transit to Ndjamena of Chad
via Bangui of the Central Africa Republic.
</P>
<P>
The plane crashed at 10 minutes to 7:00 p.m. when it was
trying to take off. All 117 passengers survived. Those with small
injuries were immediately sent to the local hospital.
</P>
<P>
Earlier indications pointed to a tire puncture as the major
cause of the accident. 
