<TEXT>
<P>
-- Colleges and universities in China's inland areas have
specially opened up subjects of traditional Chinese culture and
medicine, economy, trade, finance and law. These majors not only
suit the needs of the students from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan,
but also help them obtain employment after their graduation;
</P>
<P>
-- More Hong Kong and Taiwan compatriots are confident about
the settlement of the issue on admitting mainland academic
attainments;
</P>
<P>
-- Lower tuition fees in mainland's colleges and universities
are attracting more and more Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan students.
</P>
<P>
He said that the State Education Commission began to enroll the
students from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan in 1985. Now the number
of mainland's colleges and universities that enroll students from
these regions has risen from seven in 1985 to 110 this year.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, more than 6,000 students from Hong Kong, Macao and
Taiwan are studying in mainland's colleges and universities,
mostly spreading in the municipalities of Beijing, Shanghai,
Tianjin and the provinces of Guangdong, Fujian, Jiangsu, Hubei and
Sichuan.
</P>
<P>
For many years, the State Education Commission and other
departments concerned have taken various kinds of measures to
provide conveniences for Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan students, he
said.
</P>
<P>
the Commission will, as always, welcome and encourage more
students from these regions to come to study in China's inland
areas according to the principles of giving them the same national
treatment as mainland students, bestowing appropriate
consideration to them and guaranteeing the quality. 
