<HEADLINE> Big Three Auto Sales Soar in Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Sales at the Big Three auto makers
soared in Canada in July, setting a host of records for the month,
reports said today.
</P>
<P>
Chrysler Canada Ltd. posted the biggest gains, breaking a
20-year record with a 24-percent increase in combined car and
truck sales for July. It sold a total of 8,173 cars, and 15,093
trucks in the month.
</P>
<P>
General Motors of Canada Ltd. followed with an overall sales
increase of 20.9 percent from the same period last year. It sold a
total of 38,724 cars and light trucks in July.
</P>
<P>
Ford Motor Co. of Canada Ltd. brought up the rear with a modest
gain of three percent, to a total of 23,187 cars and trucks, the
reports said.
</P>
<P>
The auto makers are riding a wave of consumer optimism built on
low interest rates and a job market that is showing its best
improvements since 1989, said an economist at Bank of Nova Scotia.
</P>
<P>
On an annualized basis, Canadian auto makers sold 1.3 million
vehicles in July, the best showing since 1989, he added.
</P>
<P>
The import auto makers in Canada are to report their July sales
today. Double digit increases have been the norm in the past
several months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
