<HEADLINE> PLA Asked to Safeguard Party's Authority </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, August 6 (Xinhua) -- A senior PLA officer has called
on military forces to study President Jiang Zemin's May 29 speech,
and greet the upcoming 15th National Congress of the Chinese
Communist Party by recording new achievements.
</P>
<P>
Yu Yongbo, director. of the General Political Department of the
People's Liberation Army, issued the call today at a forum of
officers.
</P>
<P>
Yu said Jiang's speech laid the ideological and theoretical
basis for the forthcoming Party congress.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the important decisions made by the Party
Central Party follow the directions of Deng Xiaoping's theory of
building socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
"Safeguarding the authority of collective leadership is the
primary condition to promote our great cause of building socialism
with Chinese characteristics, and also is PLA's foremost political
task," said Yu.
</P>
<P>
"We must conscientiously adhere to the ideological and
political line of the Party Central Committee headed by Jiang."
</P>
<P>
Yu urged members of the PLA to study and gain a better
understanding of Jiang's speech concerning Party decisions on
further reforms, opening and economic development. He urged the
military to to support and implement all related decisions.
</P>
<P>
Yu also called for efforts to strengthen the Party
organizations in PLA grass roots units in order to ensure the
Party's absolute leadership over the PLA. 
</P>
</TEXT>
