<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Africa Beats India to Qualify for World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 6 (Xinhua) -- South Africa defeated India 3-0 in
a qualifying match here on Wednesday, thus becoming the first team
to qualify for the World Cup women's field hockey tournament next
year.
</P>
<P>
India struggled to answer to the awesome strike power of
18-year-old Pietie Coetzee, who scored all three of South Africa's
goals to bring her total to 10, including another hat-trick, in
four qualifying matches.
</P>
<P>
South Africa opened nervously without their usual fluency, and
were initially troubled by the close passing and artistry of their
opponents.
</P>
<P>
In the 21st minute, however, Coetzee put South Africa on the
board with a powerful reverse stick shot from the left that
bounced off the far post -- and her team then took control of the
game.
</P>
<P>
Ten minutes later, a free hit by Lindsey Carlisle from just
outside the circle saw Coetzee pouncing on the ball to score and
give South Africa a 2-0 interval lead.
</P>
<P>
The second half saw India penned into their own half for long
periods with Coetzee completing her hat-trick twelve minutes into
the period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
