<HEADLINE> Record Number of HK, Macao and Taiwan Students for Mainland College Entrance Exams (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The total number of the students
from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan applying for the entrance to
colleges and universities in China's inland areas this year
reached 1,286, hitting an all time high in history.
</P>
<P>
The work for the enrollment has been doing smoothly and will be
completed by the end of this month. The number of the enrollment
this year is expected to surpass that of the previous years.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed by a leading official of a department under
the State Education Commission in an interview with Xinhua here
today.
</P>
<P>
He said the above-mentioned figure represents a 45 percent more
than last year. Of 1,286 students, 283 came from Hong Kong, 738
from Macao and 247 from Taiwan, registering an increase of 73, 32
and 52 percent compared with last year, respectively.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the number of Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan students
applying for the entrance to the mainland's post-graduate schools
reached more than 670, up 22 percent from last year. Among them,
more than 330 students have already been enrolled.
</P>
<P>
The official attributed the increasing number of students from
Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan applying for the entrance to
mainland's colleges mainly to the following aspects:
</P>
<P>
-- Young people from these regions are eager to know more about
the motherland under the background of Hong Kong's return;
</P>
<P>
-- Over the past few years, frequent and close educational and
academic exchanges of China's inland areas with Hong Kong, Macao
and Taiwan have deepened mutual understanding and resulted in
changing the underestimation of the education standards in China's
inland areas;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
