<HEADLINE> Albanian World Cup Qualifier Venue to Be Decided Next Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Albania was expected to play its
World Cup qualifier against Northern Ireland in Tirana on
September 10, reports reaching here said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
World soccer's governing body FIFA said that a decision on
whether the home match of Albania could be played in Tirana would
be take on next Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Recent civil unrest in the Balkan country led FIFA to move all
Albania's home group nine ties to Spain. Matches against Germany
and the Ukraine were played there earlier in the year.
</P>
<P>
Officials of FIFA and UEFA, European soccer's governing body,
visited Albania over the past two days and held talks on the issue
with the country's soccer federation and the government. 
