<HEADLINE> Mongolia to Accelerate Economic Restructuring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The Mongolian government has
drawn up a three-year plan to accelerate the country's economic
restructuring, the Mongolian News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The plan is aimed at stabilizing the economy, reducing
inflation, boosting the private sector and reform social security.
</P>
<P>
It also aims to simplify bureaucracy and increase aid to the
needy.
</P>
<P>
The International Monetary Fund (IMF), which was involved in
the drawing up process, agreed to offer a loan of 33.4 million
U.S. dollars to support the program.
</P>
<P>
A Mongolian Finance Ministry spokesman said the plan is of
great importance in terms of helping the transition to a market
economy, preparing the ground for a stable economy and attracting
foreign investment. 
