<HEADLINE> Hun Sen to Seek King Sihanouk's Support </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Second Prime
Minister Hun Sen said today that he and newly-elected First
Prime Minister Ung Huot hope to meet King Norodom Sihanouk soon
and get his support for the key government change.
</P>
<P>
Shortly after the National Assembly voted overwhelmingly
earlier today to confirm Foreign Minister Ung Huot as the
country's first prime minister to replace Prince Norodom
Ranariddh, Hun Sen said he hoped the King would accept the
appointment.
</P>
<P>
Ung Huot, 50, said after his election that he hopes to meet
Sihanouk soon along with Hun Sen and the acting head of state,
Chea Sim.
</P>
<P>
Only 99 of parliament's 120 legislators took part in the vote,
with 86 votes for and four against Ung Huot, whose name was put
forward by Ranariddh's FUNCINPEC party as his replacement.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen said the vote, which demonstrated Ung Huot's support
from FUNCINPEC, his own Cambodian People's Party (CPP) and the
other two coalition parties, signaled the end of the country's
one-month political crisis.
</P>
<P>
He said he would cooperate with Ung Huot to prepare for a
free and fair election in May next year.
</P>
<P>
Ung Huot, who will keep his current portfolio as foreign
minister, said he would work closely with Hun Sen's People's Party
to build Cambodia into a country enjoying political stability,
economic development and social security. 
</P>
</TEXT>
