</P>
<P>
-- The Thai government said it will close half the country's
finance companies, finally admitting the severity of the
nation's financial crisis. Officials said the government had
spent at least 16 billion dollars in a desperate attempt to prop
up the shaky financial firms and 20 billion dollars to support
the currency.
</P>
<P>
-- A Mir repair mission was launched from Russia's cosmodrome
in Kazakstan, and the two-man crew is scheduled to dock with the
crippled space station Thursday. They will attempt to restore
vital electrical connections starting August 20. 
