<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment in South Chinese Region Increasing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region had 454 million US dollars worth of overseas
investment during the first half of this year, a 7.2 percent rise
over the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The increase is a result of six regulations for increasing the
use of overseas investment in the region. The policies are
expected to improve the local investment environment by ensuring
on-time repayment of overseas loans and putting an end to illegal
charges for local overseas-funded enterprises.
</P>
<P>
During the 1991-1996 period, the overseas funds in the region
amounted to nearly 4.4 billion US dollars worth, accounting for 20
percent of the local investment in fixed assets.
</P>
<P>
The region will place emphasis of the use of overseas funds in
developing local resources, transforming state enterprises, and in
infrastructure construction, mostly in the field of transportation
and energy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
