<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pacifists Protest Nukes at NATO Headquarters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Some 30 pacifists today
protested against the nuclear programs of the North Atlantic
Treaty Organization (NATO) in front of its headquarters here.
</P>
<P>
The protesters came from the Netherlands, Finland, Ukraine,
Russia, Britain, the United States, Germany as well as Belgium.
They demonstrated slogans of "Remember Hiroshima" and "Nuclear
Weapons Illegal".
</P>
<P>
One protester appealed, through a hand-held loudspeaker, to
passers-by and passing motorists that the anti-nuclear voice
should be heard.
</P>
<P>
One Dutch demonstrator, Freed Schmitter, said that these
individual pacifists gathered here for a one-day protest,
demanding NATO to abandon its nuclear programs.
</P>
<P>
"The International Court last year ruled that nuclear weapons
are illegal and NATO should abide by the ruling and give up its
nuclear weaponry prior to the year 2000," he said.
</P>
<P>
Willemyn van der Werf, also from the Netherlands, said that
there is an anti-nukes society in her country and the organization
now boasts of more than 6,000 members from around the nation.
</P>
<P>
She said that most of the protesters arrived here earlier this
month and will leave for more protests to be held at NATO military
bases and depots.
</P>
<P>
Local police deployed seven anti-riot vans and many police cars
near the alliance headquarters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
