<HEADLINE> Brazil, Cuba Win in American Cup Women's Basketball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- World champion Brazil
overpowered Columbia 114-55 while Cuba crushed Puerto Rico 103-68
on the opening day of the American Cup women's basketball
tournament in Sao Paulo on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The tournament has drawn a total of eight countries and
regions, including Brazil, Cuba, Columbia, Puerto Rico, the United
States, Canada, Argentina and Dominican Republic.
</P>
<P>
The eight teams will play in two groups on a round-robin format
with top two finishers in each group reaching the semifinals and
automatically qualifying for next year's World Championships in
Germany. 
