<HEADLINE> Pavarotti Backs Rome's Olympic Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 6 (Xinhua) -- World-known Italian tenor Luciano
Pavarotti has wholeheartedly surpport Rome's bid to host the 2004
Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Pavarotti will travel to Lausanne, Switzerland, for the
International Olympic Committee's meeting on September 5, when the
final venue will be decided.
</P>
<P>
Rome is favoured to win the bid, ahead of Athens, Cape Town,
Stockholm and Buenos Aires. 
</P>
</TEXT>
