<HEADLINE> EU Annual Inflation Slightly Up in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 6 (Xinhua) -- A 5.6-percent inflation rate in
Greece has sent the European Union's annual inflation slightly up
in June, Eurostat reported today.
</P>
<P>
The June rate was 1.6 percent, as against 1.5 percent in the
previous two months.
</P>
<P>
The Luxembourg-based Eurostat, the statistics arm of the
European communities, listed Norway and Denmark as the second and
third behind Greece with inflation at 2.9 percent and 2.2 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The lowest rates were registered in France and Austria, both at
1.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
The inflation rate for the European Economic Area (the 15 EU
countries plus Norway and Iceland) was also 1.6 percent. 
</P>
