<HEADLINE> South China Builds Science, Technology Information Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 6 (Xinhua) -- China's Guangdong Province has
built an open scientific and technological information network in
the provincial capital of Guangzhou as part of the China
Scientific and Technological Network.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of construction work on the local network,
which is hooked up to the Internet, began in 1995 and was
completed in June this year. The second phase is under
construction and is scheduled to be finished this year.
</P>
<P>
The network has connected the province's major scientific
research institutions and can provide more than 10 million pieces
of scientific and economic information. It also provides e-mail
and other network services.
</P>
<P>
It now leads the country's scientific and technological
networks with its more than 10,000 megabytes of information.
</P>
