<HEADLINE> HK Hosts Int'l Congress on Marine Science, Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 6 (Xinhua) -- A major international congress
on marine science and technology opened at the Chinese University
of Hong Kong here today.
</P>
<P>
The three-day '97 Pacific Congress on Marine Science and
Technology (PACON '97) is a major annual event of PACON
International, a non-governmental forum of concerned marine
scientists, engineers, industrial organizations and policy makers.
</P>
<P>
Some 200 marine scientists, engineers, technologists, policy
makers, economists and resource managers from the Pacific Rim
countries are attending the congress to discuss resource
development, environment issues and the sustainable development of
coastal waters and provide solutions for ocean management.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the congress said the ocean is abundant in
resources but far from well exploited. It may provide solutions
to an increasing population, shortage of resources and deterioration
of the environment.
</P>
<P>
The contribution of the ocean economy to total output value of
the world economy increased from two percent in 1970 to five
percent in 1990. It is expected to rise to about 10 percent at the
beginning of the 21st century.  
</P>
</TEXT>
