<HEADLINE> Private Sector Maintains Rapid Growth in Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The private sector in
Guangzhou, capital of south China's Guangdong Province, has
produced 1.44 billion yuan in total output value and 17.51 million
yuan worth of exports, during the first half of this year, to
become a major contributor to local economic growth.
</P>
<P>
By the end of June, the city has opened 25,000 privately-run
businesses, involving 219,800 employees, up 23.92 percent and
27.32 percent, respectively, over the same period of last year,
statistics showed.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou now has 508 private firms each with a registered capital
of over five million yuan, an increase of 156, and there are 24 private
enterprise groups, 11 more than a year ago.
</P>
<P>
The registered capital for each business has risen from 684,600
yuan to 756,900 yuan, with the number of workers each household
firm employs increasing by 9.5 to 9.76 on average.
</P>
<P>
Of the private enterprises, 17,100 are engaged in the service
sector, accounting for 75.87 percent of the total, a year-on-year
increase of 0.98 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
