<HEADLINE> Qinghai Becomes Hot Spot for Overseas Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, August 6 (Xinhua/OANA) -- Qinghai province, northwest
China, has drawn a total overseas investment of 240 million US
dollars, and approved the establishment of 143 foreign-funded
enterprises since early 1980s.
</P>
<P>
Business people from overseas have so far invested in more than
20 fields, including engineering industry, communications, tourism
and traditional handicrafts.
</P>
<P>
Fifteen countries and regions in Europe, Central and Southeast
Asia have founded 26 enterprises in the province.
</P>
<P>
Located on the Qinghai-Tibet plateau, Qinghai is one of the raw
material bases of the country with abundant reserves of petroleum,
nonferrous metals and other resources.
</P>
<P>
To improve its investment environment, the provincial
government has made great efforts to develop better transportation
and communication systems.
</P>
<P>
It has built a total of 1,100-km railway and 17,200-km
highway. Meanwhile, Xining Airport has opened flights to eight
areas.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the province has set up three development zones and a
program-controlled telephone network throughout all areas.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
