<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southwestern Chinese Province Auctions Off State Assets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The Leshan Pharmaceutical
Factory, a state enterprise, was auctioned off on July 30 in
Leshan City of Sichuan Province, southwest China, the first time
in that part of the country for a bankrupt state firm to be put on
the auction block.
</P>
<P>
The 50,000-sq.m. facility sold for 24.2 million yuan, which was
just above the minimum bid price. It employed 900 people used to
be a major medicine producer in Sichuan, capable of producing more
than 150 pharmaceutical products. It went bankrupt because of a
long history of poor management, according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
Present at the auction were State Economic and Trade Commission
officials, Ministry of Finance and State Bureau of Land
Administration officials, and interested buyers from Beijing,
Tianjin, Shanghai, and Chongqing municipalities, and other
provinces.
</P>
<P>
According to Li Minggui, chief executive of the Auction Center,
auctioning off state assets is a novelty in China, especially in
western areas. Bankrupt state companies often used to be sold at a
low price to other large state enterprises, with the participation
of the local government.
</P>
<P>
These deals created many problems, however, that were difficult
to solve. Assets of bankrupt enterprises were hard to sell, and
finding jobs for employees and paying off old company debts were
difficult.
</P>
<P>
Luo Xiling, a workers' representative told the reporter that
his fellow workers are all in favor of the auction, and they think
it could bring some vigor to the failed production and help many
laid-off workers go back to work.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhaoquan, chairman of the purchaser, a local investment
firm, welcomed the company's former employees, saying he'd like
them to stay on. He also told Xinhua that the company plans to
work with Qinghua University and Beijing University to rebuild the
factory into a production base for herbal medicines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
