<HEADLINE> Angola, Congo (K) to Tighten Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Angolan President Jose Eduardo
dos Santos said here Tuesday that the current visit of Presidnet
Laurent Kabila of Democratic Republic of Congo indicates the two
countries wish to open up a new era in their bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Santos said the friendly, united, good-neighborly and mutually
supportive relations between the two countries are not based on
expedient interests.
</P>
<P>
The two countries should join hands in their effort to get rid
of starvation, poverty, diseases, threats to political stability,
and the backwardness in science and economic development, the
president said.
</P>
<P>
Santos said that the Democratic Republic of Congo and Angola
should face up to the challenges of the 21st century together.
</P>
<P>
Most of the difficulties African countries are facing, he
said, are not easy to overcome, but his country is encouraged to
create every condition to revitalize its economy.
</P>
<P>
Kabila said in a brief speech at a banquet given in his honor
that he was very grateful to all the help Angola has offered to
his country in its "struggle for liberation", and his country
will never forget the political, diplomatic and material support
Angolan people have given to Congo, which helped bring their
victory.
</P>
<P>
Kabila arrived in Angola Tuesday for an official visit at the
invitation of his Angolan counterpart President Santos. This is
Kabila's first visit to the country since he became president of
Democratic Republic of Congo in mid-May. 
</P>
