<HEADLINE> German Unemployment Still Rising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The number of people out of work in
Germany rose to 4,354,300 in July, the German Federal Labour
Office said today.
</P>
<P>
The increase boosted the unemployment rate to 11.4 percent from
June's 11.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
While western Germany's joblessness rose by 66,000 to reach
nearly 2.99 million last month, the eastern half of the country
saw its unemployment increase by 65,800 to over 1.36 million.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the latest develment, Labour Office President
Bernhard Jagoda said there was an increasing imbalance in the
east-west job situation.
</P>
<P>
While the western German job market was stabilizing slowly, the
job situation in eastern Germany was still deteriorating, he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
