<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Korean Plane Returns to Airport Due to Engine Problem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 6 (Xinhua) -- A South Korean airliner with 273
people on board returned to Kansai airport in Osaka, western
Japan, today due to a malfunctioning engine, a report reaching
here said.
</P>
<P>
The Airbus A300 of the Korean Air Lines (KAL), which was on a
routine flight from Osaka to Seoul, recognized a problem in one of
its two engines 20 minutes after it departed the airport at about
1 p.m. local time, said airline officials.
</P>
<P>
The passengers have been evacuated and no injuries were
reported, they said. The cause of the trouble is under
investigation.
</P>
<P>
A Boeing 747 of the airline with 254 people on board crashed in
Guam early today while trying to land in a bad weather. More than
200 people were killed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
