<DOCNO> XIE19970806.0169 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rise on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Share prices rose in active
trading on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index gained 6.91 points to close at 1,958.62 points
today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 236 million units, valued
at 651.37 million Singapore dollars (about 446.14 million US
dollars). Advances overtook declines by 227 to 102, while 282
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Land continued to be the most actively traded
stock as it registered a turnover of 49.02 million units. It was
followed by the Hong Kong Land rfw97, which had 18.89 million
units traded. Jardine Matheson Holdings (JMH) 400 was next with
10.36 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 1.9 dollars to finish at 32.9 Singapore
dollars. The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign gained one
dollar to end at 28.8 Singapore dollars. The Development Bank of
Singapore (DBS) Foreign and the United Overseas Bank (UOB) Foreign
increased by 50 cents each to close at 18.8 and 15.2 Singapore
dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Courts was the biggest loser as it declined by
73 cents to end at 1.26 Singapore dollars. The Singapore Airlines
(SIA) Foreign fell by 60 cents to close at 13 Singapore dollars,
while the Thai Prime Fund finished 55 cents lower at 8.55 US
dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
