<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Improving Tibetan Areas in Sichuan Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Sichuan
Province has developed a short-term goal for developing Tibetan
areas.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan has more than 1.08 million Tibetans, the second largest
population after the Tibet Autonomous Region, mainly living in
the western part of the province.
</P>
<P>
According to a recent provincial government report, the annual
gross domestic product growth in the areas is expected to reach
9.1 percent up to the year 2000 and fiscal growth, ten percent,
helping eliminate fiscal deficits. Annual incomes of farmers and
herdsmen will reach 1,060 yuan.
</P>
<P>
In addition, an effort will be made to build basic facilities
for agriculture and animal husbandry, develop pillar industries,
and promote science and technology, education, and other public
undertakings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
