<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Siemens Nixdorf Eyes China's Information Technology Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Siemens Nixdorf
Informationssysteme AG, Europe's largest information technology
(IT) supplier, will introduce user-centered IT to China as part of
its new investment strategy for the profitable market.
</P>
<P>
The annual growth rate of China's IT market is double the world
average, something that has encouraged Siemens Nixdorf to shift
its investment focus to Asia, especially China, after
consolidating its position in Europe.
</P>
<P>
As the computer arm of Siemens AG, Siemens Nixdorf has provided
IT and services like PCs, Unix systems, automatic teller machines,
cash registers, and ticket-booking facilities for Chinese
government organizations, and the financial, banking,
manufacturing, retail sales, and transportation sectors.
</P>
<P>
It will also place emphasis on investment in power, water
supplies, automatic controls, telecoms, insurance, employment, and
infrastructure construction to get involved in the all-round
development of the Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
The company's business in China last year was seven times the
previous year's figure, and it is expected that by the year 2000 a
third of the company's sales will be in the Chinese market.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
