<DOCNO> XIE19970806.0175 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Steps up Anti-drug Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Guangzhou, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong Province in south
China claimed success in its three-month long anti-drug campaign.
</P>
<P>
From early April to mid July, the province launched a campaign
on social education, crackdown on drug-related crimes and forcing
drug addicts to have drug-quitting treatment.
</P>
<P>
With the help of the whole society, the police force uncovered
1,864 cases involving heroin marketing and smuggling, crushed 628
drug trafficing rings, arrested 3,801 drug-dealing suspects and
seized drugs of various kinds totaling 1,000 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
The campaign also found some 33,600 drug addicts, 28,000 of them
were sent to centers for forced drug-quitting treatment, another
3,100 were receiving education through labor so that they would
stop taking drugs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
