<HEADLINE> Marine and Aviation Transport Booming in Qingdao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Marine and aviation transport in
Qingdao, a city famed as a tourist resort in east China's Shandong
province, was booming in the first half of the year, according to
local officials.
</P>
<P>
From January to June, harbors in Qingdao handled more than 34
million tons of goods, a rise of 17.8 percent over the same period
of last year.
</P>
<P>
In particular, the shipping of minerals, crude oil, coal and
containers scored all-time highs.
</P>
<P>
The handling of containers in the harbor increased 31 percent,
and export and import goods rose by 24 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, over 800,000 domestic and overseas visitors entered
or left Qingdao through its airport, an increase of 14 percent.
</P>
<P>
Qingdao now has five international and regional passenger air
routes and two chartered freight air routes. There are 62 flights
in a week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
