<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong's Telecom Industry Grows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong province
recruited 1.1 million new telephone clients during the first six
months this year, putting the province's telephone subscription to
9.7 million users, said the latest issue of the Guangdong-Hong
Kong Information Daily.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that in the January-June period, the
province opened 463,000 new telephone lines, and added 393,000
users to its mobile telephone networks, with the total switching
capacity hitting 2.8 million.
</P>
<P>
In the mean time, 41,000 long-distance telephone lines were
added to the province's telecom system, and the combined switching
capacity of packet exchange network and DDN (digital and data
network) reached 151,000.
</P>
<P>
The province plans to raise the telephone subscription to 10
million in the second half this year, and further increase input
in the development of commercial telecom networks, ISDN
(integrated service digital network) and multimedia webs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
