crisis since the end of World War II, Chancellor Helmut Kohl and
Finance Minister Theo Waigel met a resolute opposition from the
Socialists and Greens to the plan of economic reforms at a special
session of the Bundestag Tuesday. The oppositions also asked for
an early general election, which has been officially scheduled for
1998. 
