<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yellow River Prepared to Meet Floods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, August 6 (Xinhua) -- In the past two months, people
living along the Yellow River, China's second largest river with
its river-bed higher than the ground in many parts, have fortified
its dams and dikes to be prepared for the coming flood season.
</P>
<P>
According to officials from the Yellow River Anti-flood Office,
the river has passed through 50 years without any major outbreak,
but the danger is still there as the river-bed is growing up year
by year due to soil-erosion in the upper reaches.
</P>
<P>
In May, the Yellow River Anti-Flood Headquarters, based in
Zhengzhou, capital city of central China's Henan province,
sponsored a meeting with officials from four provinces in the
middle and lower reaches of the river to mobilize local people to
prepare for potential floods.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, 223 sites that were damaged by last year's floods
have been repaired, while another 101 anti-flood projects have
also been completed.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the central government has invested to improve the
telecommunication condition for local anti-flood departments and a
responsibility system has been set up for local leading officials
to organize anti-flood efforts.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that floods have already occured in the
river. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970806.0181 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Increasing Generating Equipment Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai has set itself the goal
of producing electrical-generating equipment with a total capacity
of 4.8 million kw this year, and 5.4 million kw by the turn of the
century.
</P>
<P>
As the center of China's manufacturing industry, Shanghai has
provided more than 40 million kw of thermal power equipment since
1955, when the first home-made generating unit was built. The
equipment's installed capacity is equal to a fourth of the
country's total, making Shanghai one of the country's major
generating unit production bases.
</P>
<P>
Since 1990, Shanghai has had plans to make generating equipment
a leading industrial sector. The city produced generating
equipment with a total capacity of more than 4.5 million kw last
year, more than double the 1990 figure.
</P>
<P>
The city will improve new product development and the
industry's products mix by increasing the use of technology. It
will also increase the use of overseas investment and place
emphasis on producing high-capacity, high-parameter,
high-efficiency thermal power facilities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
