<HEADLINE> KF-16 Fighter Crashes in South Korea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, August 6 (Xinhua) -- An KF-16 jetfighter of the South
Korean Air Force crashed on Wednesday afternoon in Yoju, Kyonggi
Province, but no casualties were reported.
</P>
<P>
The plane, which was on a routine military drill, crashed into
farmland near Yoju City, some 65 kilometers southeast of Seoul,
according to the Yonhap News Agency.
</P>
<P>
However, the pilot was able to eject before the crash.
</P>
<P>
The crashed KF-16 was one of the 36 fighters assembled in
Samsung's domestic factory under U.S. technical assistance.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the crash was not known but investigations were
under way, said Yonhap. 
</P>
