<DOCNO> XIE19970806.0188 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ancient Pottery Figurines Unearthed in Jiangxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese archeologists have
discovered a group of 11 pottery figurines of the Song Dynasty
(960 to 1279 A.D.) in the western suburb of Linchuan city in east
China's Jiangxi province.
</P>
<P>
Experts here said all the colored pottery figurines have been
well preserved and one of them has a compass on it. The direction
calibration of the compass is still very clear.
</P>
<P>
The pottery figurines were discovered on a building site. The
11 figurines are in different shapes, representing officials in
charge of various kinds of duties.
</P>
<P>
One of them is putting his palms together, another one is
holding a long snake with his hands and others are taking long
swords.
</P>
<P>
Experts here said the discovery provided precious materials to
the research of ancient China's science development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970806.0189 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Filipino Cop Killed in Shootout With Car Thieves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- A policeman was killed and three
others were wounded in a running gun battle between the police and
car thieves in southern Metro Manila today.
</P>
<P>
The police were on patrol when they found the suspects driving
a vehicle which was apparently in the wanted list of the police.
</P>
<P>
When the police moved closer to question the suspects, the car
thieves fired on them and immediately drove away.
</P>
<P>
The ensuing chase lasted more than three hours and covered
various places in Metro Manila.
</P>
<P>
The policemen arrested a suspect and recovered a rifle and a
grenade in the car the thieves abandoned when they got stuck in
heavy traffic.  
</P>
</TEXT>
