<HEADLINE> Ung Huot Elected Cambodia's First Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia's National Assembly
today approved FUNCINPEC party's nomination of Foreign Minister
Ung Huot as the country's first prime minister to replace Prince
Norodom Ranariddh.
</P>
<P>
Ninety-nine of the 120 parliament members took part in the
voting, with 86 votes for, four against, six abstentions and three
invalidated ballots, assembly officials said.
</P>
<P>
Ung Huot, 50, who has been serving as foreign minister since
October 1994, will keep his current portfolio. 
</P>
