<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Penalizes Law-breaking Accountants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Ministry of Finance
(MOF) reported initial success in its effort to rectify the
working order in the accountancy industry starting from last April.
</P>
<P>
The MOF has spot-checked nearly 840,000 units during the past
three months, imposed fines on more than 70,000 of them found of
deception in accountancy, disqualified more than 200 accountants,
and brought 46 of them to justice.
</P>
<P>
A MOF official in charge of the nationwide examination said
that chaos still existed in accountancy of many units, and
prominent irregularities included opening false accounts,
fabricating information and having disorderly accounts.
</P>
<P>
More than 16 percent of the examined units were caught to have
opened false accounts involving more than 14 billion yuan, said
the official.
</P>
<P>
Pointing to other problems including a drain on state assets as
a result of the abuse of power by some enterprise managers, the
official called for redoubled efforts to rectify the working order
of accountancy and tighten supervision over the accountants.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
