<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi PM Returns From U.S. Trip </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina returned home this morning after 23 days of stay abroad.
</P>
<P>
Hasina left here on July 13 for Hamburg of Germany where she
spoke at the United Nations-sponsored international conference on
adult education. Two days Later, she went on to Miami, the United
States, where she stayed with her daughter, Saima Sharmeen Putul,
who gave birth to her first child on July 19.
</P>
<P>
Hasina's controversial trip was strongly criticized by the
opposition, who said the prime minister left the country at a time
when millions of her countrymen were marooned by the monsoon
rain-fed floods.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Abdus Samad Azad, who looked after the regular
routine work of the prime minister during Hasina's absence, and
other senior government officials greeted the prime minister at
the airport. 
</P>
