<HEADLINE> 435,000 Children in Dar es Salaam to Get Polio </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 6 (Xinhua) -- 434,964 children below the
age of five years in Dar es Salaam region will receive
vaccination against polio on August 8 and 9, the local Guardian
Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
The number is bigger than what was recorded last year when
414,405 children were vaccinated in the region against polio as
part of a three-year program to eliminate the disease world-wide
by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The exercise, which is done twice within four to six weeks
after the first vaccinaion, will be resumed on September 20 and
21. There will be 511 vaccination centers in the Dar es Salaam
region.
</P>
<P>
The polio immunization campaign started in Tanzania in January
last year following a detection of two polio cases at Muhimbili
Medical Center in the country by the end of 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
