<HEADLINE> Nepal Values Ties With China: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 6 (Xinhua) -- As a land-locked country, Nepal
must develop friendly ties with its neighbors, especially China,
Nepali Minister of Youth, Sports and Culture Bishnu Prasad Poudyal
said today.
</P>
<P>
While meeting the visiting Tianjin Art Troupe here, Poudyal
said Nepal and China enjoy a long history of cultural exchanges
and the art troupe's visit will play an important role in
strengthening the friendly ties.
</P>
<P>
He said Nepal can learn a lot from China, such as patriotism
and fine cultural traditions.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that the Nepali government will stick to its
position that Nepal's territory cannot be used for conducting
anti-China activities.
</P>
<P>
The minister expressed his belief that whatever happens,
Nepal-China friendly ties will continue, because as immediate
neighbors, the two countries know well and respect each other's
interests.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese art troupe arrived in Nepal Monday for a week-long
visit and performance after visiting Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Its premiere here Tuesday evening was well received by the
Nepalese audience.  
</P>
