<HEADLINE> Five Tamil Rebel Leaders Arrive in Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Five regional leaders of the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) are in Colombo to plan
their attacks in the capital city, according to police sources
here today.
</P>
<P>
These leaders are here directing operations along with 12 Black
Tigers who came here several weeks ahead, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
They further said several rebels who came to Colombo earlier on
a similar mission had left the area after the police gave wide
publicity to their arrival, thus making the people vigilant.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that another group of up to 20 rebels will be
coming here in the near future to plan attacks and disrupt the way
of life in the city.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been waging a war for a separate state in
the north and east of the country since 1983.
</P>
<P>
The police and the army have conducted several
cordon-and-search operations in the past week to capture the
rebels operating in Colombo.
</P>
<P>
Three lodges in the city were shut down by the police in the
past week.
</P>
<P>
They lodges were suspected of providing refuge for the LTTE
rebels, the sources said, adding that the police will take strict
action against all lodges in the capital.  
</P>
