<HEADLINE> Northwest China Lake Attracting Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Bositang Lake, the largest in the
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region in northwest China, has become a
popular tourist spot.
</P>
<P>
The 1,000-sq.km. lake, one of China's largest freshwater lakes,
is special with its large sandy stretch along its banks, making it
a beachside resort for the landlocked region.
</P>
<P>
When summer comes, thousands of tourists flock to the lake, 300
kilometers from Urumqi, the regional capital, and 60 kilometers
from Korla, the largest city in southern Xinjiang, to enjoy the
sunshine and swimming in water that can be around 25 degrees
centigrade.
</P>
<P>
Holiday-makers can also go boating or fishing on the few
islands, and local investors have already spent 25 million yuan (3
million US dollars) on a bathing area, restaurants, and hotels
there. 
</P>
