<HEADLINE> "No. One Beach" Becomes a Hot Tourism Destination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 6 (Xinhua) -- When asked to name the best
beach in China, many people would point to Shuidong Beach in the
Shuidong Economic Development Zone of Maoming City in south
China's Guangdong province.
</P>
<P>
It is said to be China's "No.1 beach" because the water there
is the most transparent, the 22-kilometer beach is the longest,
and it has a beach-side tree belt to protect from the wind.
</P>
<P>
After three years of construction work at a cost of two billion
yuan (240 million US dollars), the beach resort has become a
popular tourist spot, one that attracted 650,000 Chinese and
overseas tourists in the first half of the year.
</P>
<P>
The tourist resort has four parts: a beach, a water sports
area, a holiday resort area, and the central square.
</P>
<P>
The seaside beach is 12 kilometers long and can accommodate
swimmers all year round.
</P>
<P>
The sea sports area has many activities like boating and
para-sailing.
</P>
<P>
The holiday resort area has 12 tourist hotels and resorts with
700 beds, and 200 villas.
</P>
<P>
The central square area has a shopping street, swimming pools,
golf courses, and an exhibition center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
