<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- At least 20 people were injured as
a mild tremor shook Chandpur town in central Bangladesh Tuesday
night, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
As the earthquake was felt late last night, the panic-stricken
people ran helter-skelter for safety and 20 of them were reported
injured.
</P>
<P>
The magnitude of the tremor, which lasted for three seconds,
could not be measured as there is no Richter scale in the town, an
official at the Meteorology Department said.
</P>
<P>
A mild tremor was also felt in the capital Dhaka Tuesday night,
city dwellers said. But the Met Office could not confirm it as the
seismology center is located in coastal city Chittagong, which
remains open from 9 a.m. to 5 p.m.  
</P>
