<DOCNO> XIE19970806.0263 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Oxygen Generators Break Down on Mir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Two oxygen generators on board the
Mir space station have failed, a spokesman for the Russian ground
control center said today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the craft's oxygen-producing electrolysis
equipment broke down a few days ago, but he described the incident
as routine.
</P>
<P>
It will not affect the program of work on board the craft, the
AFP quoted him as saying.
</P>
<P>
The current three crew members, two Russian cosmonauts and
their American colleague Michael Foale, have been making repairs
and are now using back-up canisters to produce oxygen.
</P>
<P>
Yesterday, two Russian cosmonauts blasted off frofrom the
Baikonur cosmodrome in Kazakhstan to replace the current crew and
make vital repairs to the station.
</P>
<P>
Mir, which is in its 11th year in space, suffered serious
damage on June 25 when it collided with its resupply ship. The
station has been running on reduced power since then. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
