<DOCNO> XIE19970806.0264 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukraine-U.S. Naval Exercises to go Ahead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine's Defense Minister, Alexander
Kuzmuk, says the Sea Breeze-97 naval exercises with the United
States and other North Atlantic Treaty Organization countries will
begin on schedule.
</P>
<P>
Kuzmuk had expressed surprise at the amount of attention paid
to the maneuvers, saying they were routine military exercises,
local reports said.
</P>
<P>
Sea Breeze-97, to be held from August 26 to 30, faces grim
opposition from the parliament. Some legislators called the
exercises unconstitutional because the constitution declared the
country to be a non-aligned state.
</P>
<P>
Residents, especially those in the city of Sevastopol, who are
mostly Russians, are angry about the exercise which involves the
United States. Russia refused to join the exercises.
</P>
<P>
Kuzmuk said the exercise would be launched in Donuzla as
planned. The exercise would start with a "mini-Olympiad" in
commemoration of Ukraine's Independence Day on August 24, the
national news agency said.
</P>
<P>
Kuzmuk said the Ukrainian Ministry of Emergency would also
participate in exercises involving the organization of field
hospitals and demonstration of rescue equipment.
</P>
<P>
Fourteen Ukrainian navy vessels, two ships from the United
States and each of the other participating countries will join the
exercises which, organizers said, were aimed at rehearsing joint
operations for natural disasters and rescue operations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
