<HEADLINE> Peru Gets $6.8 Billion of Foreign Investment in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Direct foreign investment in Peru
reached 6.87 billion U.S. dollars in July, Peruvian National
Commission for Foreign Investment and Technology said today.
</P>
<P>
This reflects an increase of 120 million dollars over June, the
comission said.
</P>
<P>
Spain remains as the biggest investor with a total of 2.27
billion dollars, accounting for 34 percent. Its investment mainly
went to telecommunications, energy and finance.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. takes up 20 percent of the investment in Peru, while
Britain has 17 percent. Other investor countries are the
Netherlands, Chile and Panama. 
</P>
