<HEADLINE> China Newspaper Highlights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The following are highlights of
major Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The front page carried an article saying that the
fundamental task for the Communist Party of China (CPC) and the
entire Chinese people is to concentrate on developing social
productive forces.
</P>
<P>
-- The front page reprinted a long article titled "Building up a
unified communication and transportation system", which was
written by Premier Li Peng and published on Tuesday's Economic
Daily. The Premier said in the article that China should try to
build a nationwide comprehensive network of transportation.
</P>
<P>
-- The entire Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA) and the
armed police forces in recent days studied carefully the keynote
speech delivered by President Jiang Zemin at the conference
marking the 70th anniversary of the founding of the PLA on August
1.
</P>
<P>
-- The municipal government of Beijing has decided to launch a
major campaign between mid August and early October to crack down
upon pornographic and illegal publications and create a favorable
environment for the upcoming 15th National Congress of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- A front page story said that over the past five years since
the 14th CPC National Congress decided to develop a socialist
market economy, reforms in China's state-owned enterprises have
enjoyed steady progress on the basis of active pioneering and bold
practice.
</P>
<P>
-- A national conference on the work of protecting
revolutionary relics was held in Nanchang, capital city of east
China's Jiangxi Province on August 3. Premier Li Peng sent a
letter of congratulations to the conference.
</P>
<P>
-- China's largest city Shanghai has played an active role in
supporting the economic development of the country's central and
western areas. To date, the city has invested 3.5 billion yuan
(about 400 million US dollars) in and provided over 200 million
yuan of assistance for the central and western areas.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- A set of new regulations aimed at expediting a thorough
reform of funeral and burial ritual in China has been put into
effect.
</P>
<P>
-- The Ministry of Civil Affairs and the Foreign Ministry have
promulgated Regulations on the Management of Marriage
Registrations by Chinese Staying in Foreign Countries.
</P>
<P>
-- The Ministry of Public Security this week urged to reduce
the danger of fires in petrol-chemical firms and other inflammable
and explosion-prone areas.
</P>
<P>
-- Over the past five years, the CPC Central Committee has made
tremendous efforts to raise the quality of leading officials and
select outstanding young officials. Effective measures introduced
since the last CPC national congress in 1992 have strengthened
efforts to build the Party's leading bodies and official ranks.
</P>
</TEXT>
