<HEADLINE> New Head of Xinhua News Agency's Hong Kong Branch Leaves for Post </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Jiang Enzhu, newly-appointed
director of the Xinhua News agency's Hong Kong Branch, left here
for Hong Kong today to succeed Zhou Nan.
</P>
<P>
Jiang was born in Jiangsu Province and graduated from the
English Department of the Beijing Institute of Foreign Languages
in 1964.
</P>
<P>
He served as the Second Secretary of the Chinese Embassy in
London, and deputy director and director of the Western European
Affairs Department of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs.
</P>
<P>
In 1990, Jiang became Assistant Foreign Minister, then Vice
Foreign Minister from December, 1991 to December, 1995.
</P>
<P>
From April to November, 1993, he took part in the Sino-British
talks on the 1994/1995 elections in Hong Kong as a Chinese
representative.
</P>
<P>
In July of that year, Jiang became Vice Chairman of the
Preliminary Working Committee of the Preparatory Committee for the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
He served as Chinese Ambassador to Britain from December, 1995
to January of this year.
</P>
<P>
He has been described as "a Chinese official versed in English
and Hong Kong affairs and also amiable and easy to approach."
</P>
</TEXT>
