<HEADLINE> Innovation Programme Improves Efficiency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Technicians and workers in
State-owned firms are taking part in a sweeping programme to
improve efficiency by developing up-to-date technology, today's
"China Daily" reports.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-based English newspaper quotes Cui Jianping, an
official of the Chinese Association of Science and Technology
(Cast) as saying that initiated by Cast, the State Economic and
Trade Commission and the State Planning Commission, the programme
is focusing on saving energy and improving efficiency.
</P>
<P>
Statistics indicate that among the 10,000 State-owned
enterprises, technicians and workers developed 730,000 production
techniques each year, of which 160,000 were put into operation,
helping their firms earn over 1.3 billion US dollars in profits.
</P>
<P>
The programme has concentrated on improving efficiency, saving
energy, reducing costs, improving product quality, introducing
high-tech procedures, developing new products, upgrading
traditional industrial processes and streamlining management.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises give support in funds and equipment to fuel
technology innovation, and award technicians and workers according
to their contributions to the improvement of technology, the paper
says. 
</P>
</TEXT>
