<HEADLINE> Snowfalls Kill 5,000 Heads of Domestic Animal in Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Heavy snowfalls in Argentina
killed about 5,000 heads of domestic animal including cattle,
cows, horses and goats.
</P>
<P>
The recent snowfalls occurred in Southern Mendoza province
located at verge of Andes mountain range, according to a release
issued by the National gendarmery ecological patrol chief
Pablo Lebenir.
</P>
<P>
He said the numbers were calculated through a survey done in
74 breeding houses.
</P>
<P>
The official said the ecological patrol will continue
investigating 300 more breeding houses and to supply them with
forage and vaccines to prevent domestic animals from dying.
</P>
</TEXT>
