<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Typhoon Causes Floods, Two Deaths in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- A powerful typhoon sweeping across
the Philippines brought in heavy floods and left two deaths at the
height of its fury Tuesday, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report said the typhoon, coded Huling and the country's
second typhoon this year, has been lashing the country over the
past two days.
</P>
<P>
Due to the heavy floods and strong winds it brought in, a
driver fell off a bridge before a 34-year-old woman drowned when
the ferry boat she was riding capsized Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The report added that classes at elementary and secondary
schools in Manila were suspended while some colleges and
universities canceled scheduled exams. Traffic in parts of Manila
also came to a standstill.
</P>
<P>
The country's weather bureau said Huling is expected to move at
about 330 kilometers to China and Japan's Okinawa this afternoon.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970806.0282 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Finland Suspends Contacts With Bosnian Ambassador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Finland decided today to suspend
contacts with the Bosnian ambassador to Finland, Izet Serdarevic,
following the example of Western countries in toughening policy
towards Bosnia over its failure to meet peace treaty deadlines.
</P>
<P>
The Finnish decision followed a proposal by Luxembourg, which
holds the rotating presidency of the 15-nation European Union,
said a communique issued by the Finnish Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The decision also requires Finnish diplomatic missions
stationed abroad to suspend contacts with Bonsnian ambassadors,
but allows them to maintain contacts with Bosnian embassies.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few days, a number of major Western states have
suspended contacts with Bosnian ambassadors because Bosnian
leaders failed to meet an August 1 deadline for the joint
Moslem-Serb-Croat presidency to agree on the appointment of
ambassadors.
</P>
<P>
Finland hopes its decision to suspend contacts with the Bosnian
ambassador will serve to prompt Bosnia's political leaders to make
an early decision on the issue, said the communique. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
