<HEADLINE> Scotland Draws with New Zealand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Scotland secured their chance into
next year's finals of World Cup hockey tournament as they drew 1-1
with New Zealand at the qualifying meetings here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In the other two matches on Tuesday, China drew with Spain 1-1
while Group B leader Russia trounced Zimbabwe 8-0.
</P>
<P>
Scotland led most of the time in the match through Alsion Grant
who scored in the 10th minute with Sue Fraser's assist. New
Zealand tied the scores with a come-back goal from Robyn Mathews
when she got a simple free hit at the top of the circle to score
in the 56th minute.
</P>
<P>
Scottish coach Mike Gilbert was pleased with the result after
his team was beaten by Russia 0-1 and thrashed by Zimbabwe 0-9.
</P>
