<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rain Comes to East China Peninsula </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The rainfall between August 2 and 4
has helped to ease the serious drought on east China's Jiaodong
Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The local meteorological department recorded 30 mm of
precipitation over a three day period in the northwestern part of
the peninsula, with 70 mm recorded in southeastern areas.
</P>
<P>
The peninsula, one of the country's major grain and edible oil
production bases, has been in the midst of serious drought over
the past two months, with Yantai recording total precipitation of
only 36 mm, a mere 10 percent compared to last year's same
period. As a result, some small reservoirs, ponds and rivers in
the area virtually dry.
</P>
<P>
Experts say the recent rainfall will help to save autumn
crops, but warn that the dry spell will most likely continue.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970806.0294 </DOCNO>
