<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Venezuela-U.S. Meeting Cancelled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Venezuela and the United States
cancelled their scheduled August meeting in Caracas for a
bilateral accord aimed to avoid double taxation.
</P>
<P>
The deadlock came after poor results from a Washington meeting
a week ago among representatives of American Tresury and
Venezuela National Integrated Service of Tax Administration
(SENIAT) Committee, according to a committee's spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The August talks are expected to close the discussion on the
accord to avoid double taxation, to be signed October in Caracas,
during U.S. President Bill Clinton's visit to Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, the aborted meeting will be replaced
by written informal contacts to "interchange new ideas".
</P>
<P>
They claimed the cancellation leaves almost no chances to reach
a final accord to be signed during Clinton's visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
