<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Appreciates Pak Efforts to Improve Ties with </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice Foreign Minister
Tang Jiaxuan today highly appreciated Pakistan's unremitting
efforts in seeking improvement of its relations with India.
</P>
<P>
"We not only attach great importance to the relations between
Pakistan and India but also appreciate the long-standing and
unremitting efforts made by our Pakistani friends in seeking a
peaceful resolution of the Kashmir question," Tang told
journalists upon his arrival at the airport here tonight for a
two-day visit to Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Tang, who is on his sixth visit to Pakistan, also lauded
Islamabad's efforts in the resumption of talks between Pakistan
and India at the level of foreign secretary and at higher levels.
</P>
<P>
"Recently there has been relaxation in the relations between
India and Pakistan to which we attach great importance," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also called for more exchanges of bilateral visit by
officials of Pakistan and China.
</P>
<P>
"Since Pakistan and China are close neighbors, officials of the
two countries should also pay more visits to each other just like
calling on relatives," Tang said.
</P>
<P>
"Every time I visit Pakistan, I feel like home-coming," he
said.
</P>
<P>
When answering a question, Tang said, "As a close neighbor of
Afghanistan's, China has great interest in the evolution of the
situation in that country."
</P>
<P>
"We highly appreciate the constructive efforts made by the
international community including Pakistan for the restoration of
peace in Afghanistan," he said.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani Foreign Secretary Shamshad Ahmad who greeted Tang at
the airport, said at the same brief news conference that the
relationship between Pakistan and China is based on solid
foundations.
</P>
<P>
"We are proud of this 'all weather' friendship which has
withstood all tests of time," Shamshad said.
</P>
<P>
He believed that Tang's current visit "will give another boost
to this relationship".
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Pakistan, Tang Jiaxuan will hold extensive
talks with Pakistan's senior officials on bilateral, regional and
international issues of mutual interest. He will also call on
Pakistani President Farooq Leghari and Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
