<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Edges Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Blue-chip stocks struggled again
on Wall Street today after last week's record-setting advance, but
technology issues and smaller-company shares helped lift some
measures to new highs.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average fell by 10.91 points to
8,187.54 at the closing.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 9-to-7 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 525.66 million
shares as against 456.00 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 2.07 to 952.37, and
the NYSE composite index rose 1.03 to 492.96.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 16.08 to 1,621.53, a record
high for the fifth consecutive session, and the American Stock
Exchange composite index rose 4.06 to 650.65, padding Monday's
record finish. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
