<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tudjman Sworn In for 2nd Term </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Croatian President Franjo
Tudjman today was sworn in for the second five-year term in
office.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the swearing-in ceremony, Tudjman said that Croatia
attaches special importance to cooperation with the United States
and the European Union and pays special attention to the
development of friendly relations with Central European countries
as well as with China, Russia and Islamic countries.
</P>
<P>
Croatia gives consistent support to implementation of the
Dayton peace agreement for Bosnia and of the Washington agreement
on the Croatia-Muslim federation in Bosnia, he said.
</P>
<P>
Turning to domestic subjects, Tudjman said that with the
eventual return of Eastern Slavonia, Croatia has won the war to
preserve territorial integrity and can turn to reconstruction with
all its means.
</P>
<P>
Efforts in economic development should be directed towards
increasing production and employment as well as towards
modernization and greater efficiency of all economic factors, the
Croatian president said. He set 6 to 7 percent as the goal for
annual economic growth of Croatia in the next few years.
</P>
<P>
Tudjman also pledged uncompromising fight against all forms of
bribery and corruption as well as economic crimes.
</P>
<P>
The Croatian president was reelected by an overwhelming
majority in the June 15 general elections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
